'''Edna Garabedian''' is an American [[opera]]tic [[mezzo-soprano]], [[voice teacher]], and [[opera director]].
== Biography == Born to Armenian immigrants to the United States in [[Fresno, California]],<ref>"Edna Garabedian Returns For Messiah", ''[[The Fresno Bee]]'', 21 December 1990</ref> Garabedian studied singing with [[William Vennard]] at the [[University of Southern California]], [[Lotte Lehmann]] at the [[University of California, Santa Barbara]], Anna Hamlin in New York City, and [[Rosa Ponselle]] in Baltimore.<ref>"Home At Last Edna Garabedian's Fresno Roots Are Deep, Emotionally And Musically", ''The Fresno Bee'', 25 January 1998</ref> In 1961 she won the [[Metropolitan Opera National Council Auditions]].<ref>[http://www.metoperafamily.org/uploadedFiles/MetOpera/auditions/national_council_auditions/past_winners/2010_natcouncilwinners.pdf List of winners of the Metropolitan Opera National Council Auditions]</ref> She made her professional opera debut in 1965 as Santuzza in [[Pietro Mascagni]]'s ''[[Cavalleria rusticana]]'' with the [[New York City Opera]]. She went on to sing leading roles with the [[Baltimore Opera Company]], the [[Bavarian State Opera]], the [[Frankfurt Opera]], the [[Houston Grand Opera]], the [[Lyric Opera of Chicago]], the [[San Diego Opera]], the [[San Francisco Opera]], the [[Staatsoper Stuttgart]], the [[Staatstheater Kassel]], and [[Theater Bonn]] among others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hosting.operissimo.com/triboni/exec?method=com.operissimo.artist.webDisplay&id=ffcyoieagxaaaaabansx&xsl=webDisplay&searchStr=Garabedian|title=Edna Garabedian|work=[[Operissimo concertissimo]]}}</ref>
In 2000 Garabedian founded the [[California Opera Association]] of which she currently remains Artistic Director. She is a former faculty member of the voice departments at [[American University]], [[California State University, Fresno]], [[Northern Illinois University]], and the [[University of San Francisco]].<ref>[http://www.calopera.org/faculty.html Biography of Edna Garabedian at www.calopera.org]</ref>
